						               													<description>A boardgame that is based on the real Operation Storm, from 1995, when the Croatian army liberated Knin from the Serbian-Chetnik aggressor. This game is shows the heroic Operation Storm in a educational way so that the heroic acts of Croatian soldiers may never be forgotten.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is meant for 4 players, and each one has its figure and throws the dice. Depending on the dice result, player takes over the fields on the board, and the start position is in the area of Croatian Kostajnica. All along the line where Croatian army passed are drawn tanks aswell as Croatian soldiers and Serbian-Chetnik occupators. The winner is the first one that liberates the city of Knin. There is a pamphlet with real-life historical facts about Operation Storm.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By this educational and fun system the goal of this boardgame is to commemorate the heroism of the Croatian Armed Forces during the Operation Storm, and may it never be forgotten.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
